<section>
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Why I built Balances</h2>
    <div class="note">
      <p>
        I’ve been recording my household’s finances since 2011 — before I was married, and with real
        discipline since my second year of marriage. I did it in GNU Cash for about three years,
        then a self-hosted Firefly III, then Google Sheets. The daily cadence broke me every time:
        sit down at the computer, enter the day’s transactions, dread the ones I’d missed. The
        spreadsheets survived longest — and grew to twelve workbooks.
      </p>
      <p>
        Balances replaces all of it with one app and one habit I can actually keep: once a month, I
        enter the balances. I built it for my own household first, and building it in the open —
        sharpening my engineering practice along the way — means you can use it for yours.
      </p>
      <p class="sig">— Raditya (kerti), maintainer</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

